{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1018,"text":"On my desk in my office, I keep a small clay pot"},{"time":5322,"text":"that I made in college. It's raku, which is a kind of pottery"},{"time":9785,"text":"that began in Japan centuries ago as a way of"},{"time":14292,"text":"making bowls for the Japanese tea ceremony."},{"time":18339,"text":"This one is more than 400 years old."},{"time":21604,"text":"Each one was pinched or carved out of a ball of clay,"},{"time":26068,"text":"and it was the imperfections that people cherished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30364,"text":"Everyday pots like this cup take eight to 10 hours to fire."},{"time":38436,"text":"I just took this out of the kiln last week, and the kiln itself"},{"time":41545,"text":"takes another day or two to cool down, but raku"},{"time":46029,"text":"is really fast. You do it outside, and you take the kiln"},{"time":50832,"text":"up to temperature. In 15 minutes, it goes to 1,500 degrees,"},{"time":55387,"text":"and as soon as you see that the glaze has melted inside,"},{"time":59045,"text":"you can see that faint sheen, you turn the kiln off,"},{"time":61863,"text":"and you reach in with these long metal tongs,"},{"time":64450,"text":"you grab the pot, and in Japan, this red-hot pot"},{"time":68935,"text":"would be immediately immersed in a solution of green tea,"},{"time":73849,"text":"and you can imagine what that steam would smell like."},{"time":77081,"text":"But here in the United States, we ramp up the drama"},{"time":80246,"text":"a little bit, and we drop our pots into sawdust,"},{"time":83911,"text":"which catches on fire, and you take a garbage pail,"},{"time":86935,"text":"and you put it on top, and smoke starts pouring out."},{"time":91847,"text":"I would come home with my clothes reeking of woodsmoke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96727,"text":"I love raku because it allows me to play with the elements."},{"time":101825,"text":"I can shape a pot out of clay and choose a glaze,"},{"time":106321,"text":"but then I have to let it go to the fire and the smoke,"},{"time":110625,"text":"and what's wonderful is the surprises that happen,"},{"time":113090,"text":"like this crackle pattern, because it's really stressful"},{"time":116363,"text":"on these pots. They go from 1,500 degrees"},{"time":118974,"text":"to room temperature in the space of just a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123053,"text":"Raku is a wonderful metaphor for the process of creativity."},{"time":129004,"text":"I find in so many things that tension between"},{"time":132769,"text":"what I can control and what I have to let go"},{"time":136204,"text":"happens all the time, whether I'm creating a new radio show"},{"time":139998,"text":"or just at home negotiating with my teenage sons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145083,"text":"When I sat down to write a book about creativity,"},{"time":149057,"text":"I realized that the steps were reversed."},{"time":151541,"text":"I had to let go at the very beginning, and I had to"},{"time":155190,"text":"immerse myself in the stories of hundreds of artists"},{"time":159794,"text":"and writers and musicians and filmmakers, and as I listened"},{"time":164269,"text":"to these stories, I realized that creativity"},{"time":169581,"text":"grows out of everyday experiences"},{"time":172909,"text":"more often than you might think, including"},{"time":176613,"text":"letting go."},{"time":179533,"text":"It was supposed to break, but that's okay. (Laughter) (Laughs)"},{"time":183323,"text":"That's part of the letting go, is sometimes it happens"},{"time":186272,"text":"and sometimes it doesn't, because creativity also grows"},{"time":189677,"text":"from the broken places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192454,"text":"The best way to learn about anything"},{"time":195101,"text":"is through stories, and so I want to tell you a story"},{"time":199135,"text":"about work and play and about four aspects of life"},{"time":204317,"text":"that we need to embrace"},{"time":206713,"text":"in order for our own creativity to flourish."},{"time":210781,"text":"The first embrace is something that we think,"},{"time":212797,"text":"\"Oh, this is very easy,\" but it's actually getting harder,"},{"time":217003,"text":"and that's paying attention to the world around us."},{"time":220998,"text":"So many artists speak about needing to be open,"},{"time":225453,"text":"to embrace experience, and that's hard to do when"},{"time":228893,"text":"you have a lighted rectangle in your pocket that"},{"time":232511,"text":"takes all of your focus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236098,"text":"The filmmaker Mira Nair speaks about growing up"},{"time":240238,"text":"in a small town in India. Its name is Bhubaneswar,"},{"time":244843,"text":"and here's a picture of one of the temples in her town."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248536,"text":"Mira Nair: In this little town, there were like 2,000 temples."},{"time":251408,"text":"We played cricket all the time. We kind of grew up"},{"time":254264,"text":"in the rubble. The major thing that inspired me,"},{"time":257520,"text":"that led me on this path, that made me a filmmaker eventually,"},{"time":261168,"text":"was traveling folk theater that would come through the town"},{"time":264720,"text":"and I would go off and see these great battles"},{"time":268032,"text":"of good and evil by two people in a school field"},{"time":271448,"text":"with no props but with a lot of, you know,"},{"time":273984,"text":"passion, and hashish as well, and it was amazing."},{"time":277679,"text":"You know, the folk tales of Mahabharata and Ramayana,"},{"time":280473,"text":"the two holy books, the epics that everything comes out of"},{"time":283968,"text":"in India, they say. After seeing that Jatra, the folk theater,"},{"time":287498,"text":"I knew I wanted to get on, you know, and perform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292488,"text":"Julie Burstein: Isn't that a wonderful story?"},{"time":294395,"text":"You can see the sort of break in the everyday."},{"time":296815,"text":"There they are in the school fields, but it's good and evil,"},{"time":299534,"text":"and passion and hashish. And Mira Nair was a young girl"},{"time":305067,"text":"with thousands of other people watching this performance,"},{"time":308665,"text":"but she was ready. She was ready to open up"},{"time":311615,"text":"to what it sparked in her, and it led her,"},{"time":314744,"text":"as she said, down this path to become"},{"time":317359,"text":"an award-winning filmmaker."},{"time":320162,"text":"So being open for that experience that might change you"},{"time":322983,"text":"is the first thing we need to embrace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325916,"text":"Artists also speak about how some of their most powerful work"},{"time":331695,"text":"comes out of the parts of life that are most difficult."},{"time":336567,"text":"The novelist Richard Ford speaks about"},{"time":340221,"text":"a childhood challenge that continues to be something"},{"time":344263,"text":"he wrestles with today. He's severely dyslexic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349023,"text":"Richard Ford: I was slow to learn to read, went all the way"},{"time":351930,"text":"through school not really reading more than the minimum,"},{"time":355762,"text":"and still to this day can't read silently"},{"time":358290,"text":"much faster than I can read aloud,"},{"time":361138,"text":"but there were a lot of benefits to being dyslexic for me"},{"time":364914,"text":"because when I finally did reconcile myself to how slow"},{"time":368059,"text":"I was going to have to do it, then I think I came very slowly"},{"time":372554,"text":"into an appreciation of all of those qualities of language"},{"time":376086,"text":"and of sentences that are not just the cognitive"},{"time":378898,"text":"aspects of language: the syncopations, the sounds of words,"},{"time":382011,"text":"what words look like, where paragraphs break,"},{"time":383854,"text":"where lines break. I mean, I wasn't so badly dyslexic that"},{"time":386881,"text":"I was disabled from reading. I just had to do it"},{"time":389819,"text":"really slowly, and as I did, lingering on those sentences"},{"time":394362,"text":"as I had to linger, I fell heir to language's other qualities,"},{"time":398722,"text":"which I think has helped me write sentences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401986,"text":"JB: It's so powerful. Richard Ford, who's won the Pulitzer Prize,"},{"time":406066,"text":"says that dyslexia helped him write sentences."},{"time":411218,"text":"He had to embrace this challenge, and I use that word"},{"time":413989,"text":"intentionally. He didn't have to overcome dyslexia."},{"time":418102,"text":"He had to learn from it. He had to learn to hear the music"},{"time":421610,"text":"in language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424674,"text":"Artists also speak about how pushing up against"},{"time":429244,"text":"the limits of what they can do, sometimes pushing"},{"time":432638,"text":"into what they can't do, helps them focus"},{"time":435986,"text":"on finding their own voice."},{"time":439225,"text":"The sculptor Richard Serra talks about how,"},{"time":443370,"text":"as a young artist, he thought he was a painter,"},{"time":446290,"text":"and he lived in Florence after graduate school."},{"time":450569,"text":"While he was there, he traveled to Madrid,"},{"time":453138,"text":"where he went to the Prado to see this picture"},{"time":455852,"text":"by the Spanish painter Diego Velázquez."},{"time":459612,"text":"It's from 1656, and it's called \"Las Meninas,\""},{"time":464716,"text":"and it's the picture of a little princess"},{"time":466925,"text":"and her ladies-in-waiting, and if you look over"},{"time":470612,"text":"that little blonde princess's shoulder, you'll see a mirror,"},{"time":473988,"text":"and reflected in it are her parents, the King and Queen"},{"time":477285,"text":"of Spain, who would be standing where you might stand"},{"time":480690,"text":"to look at the picture."},{"time":482465,"text":"As he often did, Velázquez put himself in this painting too."},{"time":487532,"text":"He's standing on the left with his paintbrush in one hand"},{"time":492225,"text":"and his palette in the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494629,"text":"Richard Serra: I was standing there looking at it,"},{"time":496657,"text":"and I realized that Velázquez was looking at me,"},{"time":499267,"text":"and I thought, \"Oh. I'm the subject of the painting.\""},{"time":503262,"text":"And I thought, \"I'm not going to be able to do that painting.\""},{"time":505514,"text":"I was to the point where I was using a stopwatch"},{"time":508715,"text":"and painting squares out of randomness,"},{"time":513153,"text":"and I wasn't getting anywhere. So I went back and dumped"},{"time":515171,"text":"all my paintings in the Arno, and I thought, I'm going to just start playing around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518401,"text":"JB: Richard Serra says that so nonchalantly, you might"},{"time":521233,"text":"have missed it. He went and saw this painting by a guy"},{"time":524841,"text":"who'd been dead for 300 years, and realized,"},{"time":528609,"text":"\"I can't do that,\" and so Richard Serra went back"},{"time":532481,"text":"to his studio in Florence, picked up all of his work"},{"time":535312,"text":"up to that point, and threw it in a river."},{"time":539115,"text":"Richard Serra let go of painting at that moment,"},{"time":543051,"text":"but he didn't let go of art. He moved to New York City,"},{"time":546577,"text":"and he put together a list of verbs"},{"time":549491,"text":"— to roll, to crease, to fold —"},{"time":552779,"text":"more than a hundred of them, and as he said,"},{"time":555475,"text":"he just started playing around. He did these things"},{"time":557512,"text":"to all kinds of material. He would take a huge sheet of lead"},{"time":560829,"text":"and roll it up and unroll it. He would do the same thing"},{"time":564627,"text":"to rubber, and when he got to the direction \"to lift,\""},{"time":569803,"text":"he created this, which is in the Museum of Modern Art."},{"time":574901,"text":"Richard Serra had to let go of painting"},{"time":577861,"text":"in order to embark on this playful exploration"},{"time":581301,"text":"that led him to the work that he's known for today:"},{"time":584571,"text":"huge curves of steel that require our time and motion"},{"time":590149,"text":"to experience. In sculpture,"},{"time":593886,"text":"Richard Serra is able to do what he couldn't do in painting."},{"time":597157,"text":"He makes us the subject of his art."},{"time":601653,"text":"So experience and challenge"},{"time":605589,"text":"and limitations are all things we need to embrace"},{"time":609249,"text":"for creativity to flourish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611845,"text":"There's a fourth embrace, and it's the hardest."},{"time":615405,"text":"It's the embrace of loss,"},{"time":617765,"text":"the oldest and most constant of human experiences."},{"time":622055,"text":"In order to create, we have to stand in that space"},{"time":624878,"text":"between what we see in the world and what we hope for,"},{"time":628678,"text":"looking squarely at rejection, at heartbreak,"},{"time":633485,"text":"at war, at death."},{"time":636059,"text":"That's a tough space to stand in."},{"time":638449,"text":"The educator Parker Palmer calls it \"the tragic gap,\""},{"time":643838,"text":"tragic not because it's sad but because it's inevitable,"},{"time":647805,"text":"and my friend Dick Nodel likes to say,"},{"time":650845,"text":"\"You can hold that tension like a violin string"},{"time":653789,"text":"and make something beautiful.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":657225,"text":"That tension resonates in the work of the photographer"},{"time":660363,"text":"Joel Meyerowitz, who at the beginning of his career was"},{"time":663573,"text":"known for his street photography, for capturing a moment"},{"time":666813,"text":"on the street, and also for his beautiful photographs"},{"time":670495,"text":"of landscapes -- of Tuscany, of Cape Cod,"},{"time":674179,"text":"of light."},{"time":676861,"text":"Joel is a New Yorker, and his studio for many years"},{"time":680130,"text":"was in Chelsea, with a straight view downtown"},{"time":684128,"text":"to the World Trade Center, and he photographed"},{"time":687043,"text":"those buildings in every sort of light."},{"time":691376,"text":"You know where this story goes."},{"time":695026,"text":"On 9/11, Joel wasn't in New York. He was out of town,"},{"time":697514,"text":"but he raced back to the city, and raced down to the site"},{"time":702113,"text":"of the destruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704238,"text":"Joel Meyerowitz: And like all the other passersby,"},{"time":706417,"text":"I stood outside the chain link fence on Chambers"},{"time":709317,"text":"and Greenwich, and all I could see was the smoke"},{"time":711515,"text":"and a little bit of rubble, and I raised my camera"},{"time":715185,"text":"to take a peek, just to see if there was something to see,"},{"time":718185,"text":"and some cop, a lady cop, hit me on my shoulder,"},{"time":722529,"text":"and said, \"Hey, no pictures!\""},{"time":724969,"text":"And it was such a blow that it woke me up,"},{"time":728193,"text":"in the way that it was meant to be, I guess."},{"time":732249,"text":"And when I asked her why no pictures, she said,"},{"time":734292,"text":"\"It's a crime scene. No photographs allowed.\""},{"time":737383,"text":"And I asked her, \"What would happen if I was a member"},{"time":738852,"text":"of the press?\" And she told me,"},{"time":741056,"text":"\"Oh, look back there,\" and back a block was the press corps"},{"time":745150,"text":"tied up in a little penned-in area,"},{"time":748960,"text":"and I said, \"Well, when do they go in?\""},{"time":750481,"text":"and she said, \"Probably never.\""},{"time":752963,"text":"And as I walked away from that, I had this crystallization,"},{"time":757454,"text":"probably from the blow, because it was an insult in a way."},{"time":760248,"text":"I thought, \"Oh, if there's no pictures,"},{"time":762423,"text":"then there'll be no record. We need a record.\""},{"time":765929,"text":"And I thought, \"I'm gonna make that record."},{"time":767799,"text":"I'll find a way to get in, because I don't want to"},{"time":770086,"text":"see this history disappear.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":771954,"text":"JB: He did. He pulled in every favor he could,"},{"time":776197,"text":"and got a pass into the World Trade Center site,"},{"time":778710,"text":"where he photographed for nine months almost every day."},{"time":782942,"text":"Looking at these photographs today brings back"},{"time":785886,"text":"the smell of smoke that lingered on my clothes"},{"time":788791,"text":"when I went home to my family at night."},{"time":790788,"text":"My office was just a few blocks away."},{"time":794206,"text":"But some of these photographs are beautiful,"},{"time":797822,"text":"and we wondered, was it difficult for Joel Meyerowitz"},{"time":800937,"text":"to make such beauty out of such devastation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":805279,"text":"JM: Well, you know, ugly, I mean, powerful"},{"time":808645,"text":"and tragic and horrific and everything, but"},{"time":812016,"text":"it was also as, in nature, an enormous event"},{"time":816312,"text":"that was transformed after the fact into this residue,"},{"time":821478,"text":"and like many other ruins"},{"time":823294,"text":"— you go to the ruins of the Colosseum or the ruins of a cathedral someplace —"},{"time":827143,"text":"and they take on a new meaning when you watch the weather."},{"time":831780,"text":"I mean, there were afternoons I was down there,"},{"time":833653,"text":"and the light goes pink and there's a mist in the air"},{"time":837303,"text":"and you're standing in the rubble, and I found myself"},{"time":841334,"text":"recognizing both the inherent beauty of nature"},{"time":845218,"text":"and the fact that nature, as time,"},{"time":847972,"text":"is erasing this wound."},{"time":851367,"text":"Time is unstoppable, and it transforms the event."},{"time":855201,"text":"It gets further and further away from the day,"},{"time":857530,"text":"and light and seasons temper it in some way,"},{"time":861885,"text":"and it's not that I'm a romantic. I'm really a realist."},{"time":866029,"text":"The reality is, there's the Woolworth Building"},{"time":869513,"text":"in a veil of smoke from the site, but it's now like a scrim"},{"time":875341,"text":"across a theater, and it's turning pink,"},{"time":879285,"text":"you know, and down below there are hoses spraying,"},{"time":882388,"text":"and the lights have come on for the evening, and the water"},{"time":885397,"text":"is turning acid green because the sodium lamps are on,"},{"time":889425,"text":"and I'm thinking, \"My God, who could dream this up?\""},{"time":891602,"text":"But the fact is, I'm there, it looks like that,"},{"time":895803,"text":"you have to take a picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897697,"text":"JB: You have to take a picture. That sense of urgency,"},{"time":900890,"text":"of the need to get to work, is so powerful in Joel's story."},{"time":906690,"text":"When I saw Joel Meyerowitz recently, I told him how much"},{"time":910043,"text":"I admired his passionate obstinacy, his determination"},{"time":913828,"text":"to push through all the bureaucratic red tape to get to work,"},{"time":918411,"text":"and he laughed, and he said, \"I'm stubborn,"},{"time":920587,"text":"but I think what's more important"},{"time":922991,"text":"is my passionate optimism.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":926452,"text":"The first time I told these stories, a man in the audience"},{"time":929255,"text":"raised his hand and said, \"All these artists talk about"},{"time":932745,"text":"their work, not their art, which has got me thinking about"},{"time":937483,"text":"my work and where the creativity is there,"},{"time":940151,"text":"and I'm not an artist.\" He's right. We all wrestle"},{"time":944779,"text":"with experience and challenge, limits and loss."},{"time":949395,"text":"Creativity is essential to all of us,"},{"time":951646,"text":"whether we're scientists or teachers,"},{"time":954299,"text":"parents or entrepreneurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958658,"text":"I want to leave you with another"},{"time":960835,"text":"image of a Japanese tea bowl. This one"},{"time":963929,"text":"is at the Freer Gallery in Washington, D.C."},{"time":966899,"text":"It's more than a hundred years old and you can still see"},{"time":969435,"text":"the fingermarks where the potter pinched it."},{"time":973078,"text":"But as you can also see, this one did break"},{"time":975995,"text":"at some point in its hundred years."},{"time":978715,"text":"But the person who put it back together,"},{"time":981475,"text":"instead of hiding the cracks,"},{"time":984039,"text":"decided to emphasize them, using gold lacquer to repair it."},{"time":989755,"text":"This bowl is more beautiful now, having been broken,"},{"time":994199,"text":"than it was when it was first made,"},{"time":997211,"text":"and we can look at those cracks, because"},{"time":999441,"text":"they tell the story that we all live,"},{"time":1001806,"text":"of the cycle of creation and destruction,"},{"time":1005483,"text":"of control and letting go, of picking up the pieces"},{"time":1010410,"text":"and making something new."},{"time":1012409,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}